David Listena Prickett
August 16 at 3:59 PM ·

Granite parents: We are working towards optimal communications with you! Please follow these prompts to be engaged with us so there is better daily, weekly, monthly communications. Thanks for partnering with us!!!

Looking forward to seeing our students tomorrow!!!! Remember face masks and some type of water bottle your child can refill during the day.

Also, your child's temp will be taken prior to entering their classroom.

If you drop your child off in mornings, please remember ONE WAY heading NORTH by 3rd grade, stopping in crosswalk. No parking cars in street nor blocking school buildings. 😉

New change for lunch:
.....4th, 5th, 6th, will eat with their teachers in the designated spaces in the old gym. Skip has set up tables and fans. It looks really good and is surprisingly cooler than lunchroom most days.
....7th and 8th: will meet in Old Gym before school and they will eat in the old gym with a teacher on duty.

Looking forward to our first week!🥰

Granite Baseball
July 31 at 4:51 PM ·

Ok everyone, this is defiantly not perfect but I think it will be a blast anyway. Tomorrow is the first annual Granite Alumni Softball Tournament. Attached is the bracket and the teams that I know of. I know some of the teams may have changed a little and that is fine. Make sure everyone knows that it costs $25 per player to play and you have to alternate batting order and follow the previously posted rules on positioning. You can come pay Coach Snider in the concession ( He may be officiating a bit) or pay your team captain and they can bring the money. I will have Tee shirts in the concession split up by team. All of the basic slow pitch rules are in affect. Please come ready to have fun and not cause problems. We have volunteer umpires so please treat them with respect and just have a good time. See everybody there!!!

OKPROMISE

Attention Last Years Sophomores:

Students have until June 30th to apply for OKPROMISE. Go to okhighered.org
Choose application requirements
Choose resources at the bottom
This takes you to Application
Choose Apply Now button.
Be prepared to send in your parents tax form 1040. Your household income must be $55,000 or less.

Students who have completed 8th grade and 9th can also apply. These students have until 10th grade to apply. If your parents have been without work because of COVID19, then next year may be a good time to apply.

Gaylord Louis Heck‎Granite Consolidated Alumni
May 13 at 6:55 PM ·

This year's Granite Consolidated Alumni Parade will honor our alumnist whom are front line workers. Any medical field, fire/rescue & law enforcement are included. PLEASE SUBMIT their names, school & graduation year to Louis (Inks) Heck either by dm or email to Louis@heckfarm.com
Any front line working alumnist that plans on attending, please advise of that as well so we can honor your service properly!
Parade is June 20th. Line up will be on 6th street by Baptist Church for entries at 130 pm. That will leave the end of Main Street open to line up our wonderful Fire, Police, & other town equipment. Parade will kick off at 2 pm!
If your class, group, business or kiddos on horses, 4 wheelers or bikes (or such) plan on being in, please let Louis know. All are welcome!

Granite Sophomores!!!

If you are a sophomore and are interested in OKPromise you have until June 30th to complete your paperwork. OKPromise understands some of you many have taken a drastic cut in pay because of the pandemic.

Go to www.okhighered.org/okpromise for information and an application form. You will need a copy of your 2020 federal tax return to prove your income is under $55,000.

If you have more questions, you may contact Mrs. Haley at khaley@granite.k12.ok.us.

Thank you and act now!!!

Kyle Norvell is with Addisyn Nolan and 16 others.
May 9 at 11:48 PM ·

Well this was not intended when we chose them but the Meinert’s would have ran away with the banquet this year if we would of had one. William Meinert was the Star Greenhand this year. Will was a three time state qualifier. 2 times in speeches and once in opening and closing ceremonies. He’s one more speech contest in the last year and a half then most kids win in anything. Great young man that will have an outstanding future. Next are our two honorary degree recipients. Terran Meinert was my right hand man this year. He covered my classes almost every time I was gone. He also helped to remodel the ag building and was there anytime the chapter needed him. Last but certainly not least is Mike Meinert. Without Mike, the ag building wouldn’t look the way it does now. He put the idea in my head to remodel the ag building and without his suggestion it wouldn’t look how it does now. Mike and Terran also came up on their own time and leveled the ceiling and gave great advice on the work. Thank you for your service to the chapter. Great men! Great family!

shared_text:
Kyle Norvell is with Addisyn Nolan and 14 others.
May 4 at 8:30 PM ·

Well we didn’t get to have a banquet this year but we still have great young people who earned recognition. This years “Never Settle” award winner is Karai Blakley. When Karai entered FFA last year she was a quite young lady who didn’t speak because she didn’t like the way she pronounced words. She really struggled speaking but decided to give speeches anyways. This year she spent three nights a week saying phrases I gave her to improve. She now speaks clearly and would have had an outstanding spring if not for the lockdown. Although she never had the successes like others in the chapter, she never quit, she never gave up, but most of all she never settled for anything less than her best. She understood that she wasn’t perfect but if she worked to correct her flaws she could become more so. Great young lady and hope others learn from her example.

Today was a bitter sweet day. It was the final feed day for the week and a wrap up for the school year . Thank you to all these employees for making our breakfast and lunch deliveries possible. It has been great! Thanks to our parents and community for their help and participation. Thanks Katy Murray for hand sanitizers and thermometers and Belinda Graham for allowing every student a free packet to put in their water! Huge thanks to Mr. JR (we call him the bread man) for alllll the free bread and goodies. Thanks to Teresa Hopkins for all the paper work making this possible. We are so blessed.

shared_text:
David Listena Prickett
April 23 at 9:34 AM ·

Granite Seniors:
We want to recognize and honor our seniors on Facebook. So here is a little creative project we need you guys to do. 👌
1. Have a photo shoot. We need a picture in your quarantine T-shirt for sure! (We'd also love a picture in your cap and gown. )Be creative on setting and poses. Best lighting is outside! Text or email those two pictures to Mrs. Coffin, your Sr. Sponsor.
2. Write 2-3 sentences about your plans for the future, what you love and what you will miss most about your school and your town, etc. Include this in your text/email. 👌

We will be posting these as soon we get them, hopefully 1 or 2 people a day.
Thank you! Congratulations 2020 Seniors ❤

Britannica Digital Learning is offering MORE free resources as part of their COVID-19 response.

Check our Temporary Access category on Digital Prairie's Research and Discovery page to find out how to access free e-books in the following categories:

Elementary Spanish
Elementary STEAM
Elementary ELA
Middle School Social Studies
Middle School STEAM
High School STEM
High School World History

Access will remain free through June 30, 2020, from any device you choose, both online and offline. While on the Research and Discovery page, explore all of the other free library and information resources available to every Oklahoman thanks to ODL's statewide contract with EBSCO.

Go to https://digitalprairieok.net/discover/

Granite Parents❤...So much thought and careful planning from our faculty was put in to DISTANT LEARNING for our wonderful student body. Sadly, due to increasing COVID19 in our county, NO PACKET PICKUP tomorrow, April 6th, for Distant Learning at the school. Each teacher will contact parents on how to facilitate distant learning in keeping everyone as safe as possible.🙏 Thank you for your support ❤and understanding of this ever changing COVID19 situation. Once again, we WILL get through this... together. Please join us in trying to stay as safe as possible during these worrisome times. We love and miss our students...watch for your teacher contact.👌REMEMBER: grab n go meals..8 to 10 a.m. tomorrow only this week....1 time pick up for entire week🙂

Granite Parents: Tomorrow, Monday, March 23rd, we begin our "Grab N Go" breakfast/lunch for children 0 to 18.😋Remember to drive up to our North door of our gym/cafeteria. We will provide those from 10:00 a.m.--12:30. Remember to stay in your car so we honor health guidelines.👌 Also, please inform your child Mrs. Prickett will be wearing a clear face shield or a mask while handing out meal sacks and we don't want this to scare them❤. So grateful to our cafeteria ladies for their preparations.😋 We will provide these quick meals Monday-Thursday weekly until further notice. Thank you, too, for your patience as we work through this new process. See you soon❤
